Spanakopita - House made phyllo dough pouches stuffed with spinach, greens, herbs, and feta cheese	A classic Greek savory pie or individual pouches made with flaky, house-made phyllo dough, filled with a mixture of spinach, various greens (like chard or leeks), fresh herbs (dill, parsley), and tangy feta cheese.	Appetizer / Side Dish / Light Main	\N	Phyllo dough (wheat flour, water, oil/butter), spinach, feta cheese (dairy), onions or scallions, leeks (optional), fresh dill, fresh parsley, eggs (often used as binder), olive oil or butter (dairy). [Note: Specific greens and use of egg may vary.]	t	f	f	f	t	\N	2025-05-27 15:12:59.21596	2025-05-27 15:12:59.21596	{"dietary_flags_list": ["VEGETARIAN_OPTION"], "allergen_alert_list": ["CONTAINS_WHEAT (phyllo dough)", "CONTAINS_DAIRY (feta cheese, butter if used in phyllo)", "CONTAINS_EGG (if used as binder in filling)"], "key_preparation_notes": "Savory spinach and feta pie in flaky phyllo pastry. Contains wheat and dairy. Please inquire if egg is used in the filling.", "nutritional_highlights": {"fat": {"max": 25, "min": 15, "unit": "g"}, "carbs": {"max": 35, "min": 20, "unit": "g"}, "fiber": {"max": 5, "min": 2, "unit": "g"}, "protein": {"max": 15, "min": 8, "unit": "g"}, "calories": {"max": 400, "min": 250, "unit": "kcal"}}, "guidance_for_customer_short": "Crispy, flaky, and flavorful spinach and feta phyllo pie. (Values per typical triangular portion).", "suitable_for_diet_preferences": []}	0.00	spanakopita
Kritharaki - Orzo pasta baked in the oven. A pasta side dish choice with any main	Kritharaki, also known as orzo, is a small, rice-shaped pasta. In this Greek preparation, it's typically baked in the oven, often with tomato sauce, broth, onions, and herbs, resulting in a flavorful and tender side dish.	Side Dish - Pasta	\N	Orzo pasta (wheat), tomato sauce or passata, onions, garlic (optional), olive oil, vegetable or chicken broth, oregano, salt, pepper. Sometimes cheese is added. [Note: Preparation can vary; sometimes cooked like pilaf, sometimes baked in sauce.]	t	t	f	t	t	\N	2025-05-27 15:12:59.303182	2025-05-27 15:12:59.303182	{"dietary_flags_list": ["VEGETARIAN_OPTION", "VEGAN_OPTION (if prepared without cheese/chicken broth)"], "allergen_alert_list": ["CONTAINS_WHEAT (orzo pasta)"], "key_preparation_notes": "Orzo pasta baked until tender, often in a light tomato-herb sauce. Confirm if chicken broth or cheese is used if vegan/dairy-free is required.", "nutritional_highlights": {"fat": {"max": 10, "min": 4, "unit": "g"}, "carbs": {"max": 45, "min": 30, "unit": "g"}, "fiber": {"max": 3, "min": 1, "unit": "g"}, "protein": {"max": 9, "min": 5, "unit": "g"}, "calories": {"max": 300, "min": 180, "unit": "kcal"}}, "guidance_for_customer_short": "Flavorful baked orzo pasta, a classic Greek side. (Values per 1 cup serving).", "suitable_for_diet_preferences": []}	0.00	kritharaki
Gigandes Plaki - Oven baked lima beans in a herbaceous tomato sauce	Gigandes Plaki are giant dried white lima beans (Gigantes beans) baked in a rich, herbaceous tomato sauce with onions, garlic, olive oil, and plenty of fresh herbs like dill, parsley, and oregano. A hearty and flavorful vegetarian Greek classic.	Side Dish / Vegetarian Main	\N	Giant lima beans (Gigantes beans), diced tomatoes, tomato paste, onions, garlic, olive oil, fresh parsley, fresh dill, dried oregano, celery (optional), carrots (optional), salt, pepper. [Note: Specific herbs and vegetables may vary slightly.]	t	t	t	t	t	\N	2025-05-27 15:12:59.433666	2025-05-27 15:12:59.433666	{"dietary_flags_list": ["VEGAN_OPTION", "VEGETARIAN_OPTION", "PLANT_BASED", "HIGH_PROTEIN (for a plant source)", "HIGH_FIBER", "MEDITERRANEAN_DIET"], "allergen_alert_list": [], "key_preparation_notes": "Large lima beans baked in a savory tomato and herb sauce. A staple of Greek cuisine.", "nutritional_highlights": {"fat": {"max": 20, "min": 10, "unit": "g"}, "carbs": {"max": 55, "min": 35, "unit": "g"}, "fiber": {"max": 18, "min": 10, "unit": "g"}, "protein": {"max": 20, "min": 12, "unit": "g"}, "calories": {"max": 450, "min": 280, "unit": "kcal"}}, "guidance_for_customer_short": "Hearty and delicious oven-baked giant lima beans.", "suitable_for_diet_preferences": ["VEGAN_DIET", "VEGETARIAN_DIET"]}	0.00	gigandes_plaki
Tyrokroketes - A blend of three Greek cheeses rolled into delightful tangy balls and coated with sesame seeds	Tyrokroketes are Greek cheese croquettes. They are made from a blend of tangy and melty Greek cheeses (often feta, kefalotyri, graviera), sometimes with a hint of spice or herbs, rolled into balls, coated (this version specifies sesame seeds, traditionally often breadcrumbs), and fried until golden and crispy.	Appetizer	\N	Greek cheeses (e.g., feta, kefalotyri, graviera - dairy), egg (binder), flour (wheat, for dusting/binding), sesame seeds (coating), black pepper. Oil for frying. [Note: Cheese blend and coating (sometimes breadcrumbs) can vary.]	t	f	f	f	t	\N	2025-05-27 15:12:59.521806	2025-05-27 15:12:59.521806	{"dietary_flags_list": ["VEGETARIAN_OPTION"], "allergen_alert_list": ["CONTAINS_DAIRY (various cheeses)", "CONTAINS_EGG (binder)", "CONTAINS_WHEAT (flour for dusting/binding)", "CONTAINS_SESAME (coating)"], "key_preparation_notes": "Fried cheese balls made with a blend of Greek cheeses and coated in sesame seeds. Contains dairy, egg, wheat, and sesame.", "nutritional_highlights": {"fat": {"max": 12, "min": 6, "unit": "g"}, "carbs": {"max": 8, "min": 3, "unit": "g"}, "fiber": {"max": 1, "min": 0, "unit": "g"}, "protein": {"max": 7, "min": 4, "unit": "g"}, "calories": {"max": 150, "min": 80, "unit": "kcal"}}, "guidance_for_customer_short": "Crispy, tangy, and irresistible Greek cheese balls with sesame. (Values per ball).", "suitable_for_diet_preferences": []}	0.00	tyrokroketes
Octapodi - Spanish octopus slowly braised and served simply with lemon juice, EVOO, and fresh oregano	Tender Spanish octopus, slowly braised to perfection, then often finished on the grill for a slight char. Served in a classic Greek style, dressed simply with fresh lemon juice, extra virgin olive oil (EVOO), and fresh oregano.	Appetizer / Main Course - Seafood	\N	Octopus (Spanish), olive oil, lemon juice, fresh oregano, red wine vinegar (often in braising liquid), bay leaf, salt, pepper. [Note: Braising liquid and finishing touches may vary slightly.]	f	f	t	t	t	\N	2025-05-27 15:12:59.609183	2025-05-27 15:12:59.609183	{"dietary_flags_list": ["HIGH_PROTEIN", "GRILLED (often finished on grill)"], "allergen_alert_list": ["CONTAINS_SHELLFISH (octopus is a mollusc)", "CONTAINS_SULPHITES (if vinegar/wine is used)"], "key_preparation_notes": "Octopus braised until tender, then typically grilled and dressed with lemon, olive oil, and oregano.", "nutritional_highlights": {"fat": {"max": 10, "min": 4, "unit": "g"}, "carbs": {"max": 4, "min": 1, "unit": "g"}, "fiber": {"max": 0, "min": 0, "unit": "g"}, "protein": {"max": 35, "min": 25, "unit": "g"}, "calories": {"max": 250, "min": 150, "unit": "kcal"}}, "guidance_for_customer_short": "Tender, flavorful braised and grilled octopus, a Greek delicacy. (Values per 100g serving).", "suitable_for_diet_preferences": ["MEDITERRANEAN_DIET", "PALEO_FRIENDLY"]}	7.00	octapodi
Dolmades - Grape leaves stuffed with rice and fresh herbs	Dolmades (or Dolmadakia Yialantzi if meatless) are tender grape leaves stuffed with a savory mixture of rice, onions, and copious fresh herbs like parsley, mint, and dill. They are gently simmered in a lemony broth with olive oil.	Appetizer / Side Dish	\N	Grape leaves (fresh or brined), medium-grain rice, onions, olive oil, fresh parsley, fresh mint, fresh dill, lemon juice, salt, pepper. Some variations might include pine nuts. [Note: Meat-filled versions (not Yialantzi) exist but this description implies vegetarian.]	t	t	t	t	\N	\N	2025-05-27 15:12:59.702709	2025-05-27 15:12:59.702709	{"dietary_flags_list": ["VEGAN_OPTION", "VEGETARIAN_OPTION", "PLANT_BASED"], "allergen_alert_list": ["CONTAINS_NUTS (potentially pine nuts, please inquire)", "CONTAINS_SULPHITES (brined grape leaves may contain)"], "key_preparation_notes": "Grape leaves stuffed with herbed rice. A classic vegan Greek meze. Check if pine nuts are included.", "nutritional_highlights": {"fat": {"max": 3, "min": 1, "unit": "g"}, "carbs": {"max": 9, "min": 5, "unit": "g"}, "fiber": {"max": 1.5, "min": 0.5, "unit": "g"}, "protein": {"max": 1.5, "min": 0.5, "unit": "g"}, "calories": {"max": 60, "min": 30, "unit": "kcal"}}, "guidance_for_customer_short": "Tender, flavorful rice-stuffed grape leaves. (Values per dolma).", "suitable_for_diet_preferences": ["VEGAN_DIET", "VEGETARIAN_DIET", "MEDITERRANEAN_DIET"]}	0.00	dolmades
Saganaki Cheese - Cheese is deep fried to make a crispy outside, with a melty gooey inside. Flambeed tableside! (Family style only)	A spectacular Greek appetizer where a firm, salty Greek cheese (like Kefalotyri, Kefalograviera, or Kasseri) is pan-fried or deep-fried until it has a crispy golden-brown crust and a molten, gooey interior. It is famously flambéed tableside with brandy or ouzo, and a squeeze of lemon is added to douse the flames.	Appetizer	\N	Greek cheese (e.g., Kefalotyri, Kasseri, Graviera - dairy), flour (wheat, for dredging), olive oil or butter (dairy) for frying. Brandy or Ouzo for flambé, lemon. [Note: Type of cheese used is key.]	t	f	f	f	t	\N	2025-05-27 15:14:15.498164	2025-05-27 15:14:15.498164	{"dietary_flags_list": ["VEGETARIAN_OPTION", "INTERACTIVE_PRESENTATION"], "allergen_alert_list": ["CONTAINS_DAIRY (cheese, butter if used)", "CONTAINS_WHEAT (flour for dredging)", "CONTAINS_SULPHITES (from brandy/ouzo if used)"], "key_preparation_notes": "Fried Greek cheese, flambéed tableside. Contains dairy and wheat. Alcohol is used in flambé.", "nutritional_highlights": {"fat": {"max": 35, "min": 20, "unit": "g"}, "carbs": {"max": 10, "min": 5, "unit": "g"}, "fiber": {"max": 1, "min": 0, "unit": "g"}, "protein": {"max": 25, "min": 15, "unit": "g"}, "calories": {"max": 450, "min": 300, "unit": "kcal"}}, "guidance_for_customer_short": "Opa! Crispy, melty fried cheese with a tableside flambé. (Family style only).", "suitable_for_diet_preferences": []}	2.00	saganaki
Baked Vegetables - Briam - Thinly sliced vegetable medley, seasoned and baked till lightly charred	Briam is a traditional Greek roasted vegetable dish. It consists of a medley of summer vegetables, such as potatoes, zucchini, eggplant, tomatoes, and onions, thinly sliced or chunked, generously drizzled with olive oil, seasoned with herbs (especially oregano), and baked until tender and slightly charred.	Side Dish / Vegetarian Main	\N	Potatoes, zucchini, eggplant, tomatoes, onions, bell peppers (optional), garlic, olive oil, dried oregano, fresh parsley, salt, pepper. [Note: Vegetable combination can vary based on seasonality.]	t	t	t	t	t	\N	2025-05-27 15:15:22.929982	2025-05-27 15:15:22.929982	{"dietary_flags_list": ["VEGAN_OPTION", "VEGETARIAN_OPTION", "PLANT_BASED", "HIGH_FIBER", "MEDITERRANEAN_DIET"], "allergen_alert_list": [], "key_preparation_notes": "A hearty medley of roasted Mediterranean vegetables baked in olive oil and herbs.", "nutritional_highlights": {"fat": {"max": 22, "min": 12, "unit": "g"}, "carbs": {"max": 35, "min": 20, "unit": "g"}, "fiber": {"max": 10, "min": 5, "unit": "g"}, "protein": {"max": 6, "min": 3, "unit": "g"}, "calories": {"max": 350, "min": 200, "unit": "kcal"}}, "guidance_for_customer_short": "Deliciously roasted Greek vegetable medley, simple and flavorful.", "suitable_for_diet_preferences": ["VEGAN_DIET", "VEGETARIAN_DIET"]}	0.00	baked_vegetables
Salata Horiatiki - A mix of tomatoes, cucumber, onion, green pepper, feta, and olives, dressed with oil and vinegar	Horiatiki Salata, or Greek Village Salad, is a rustic and refreshing salad featuring chunks of ripe tomatoes, crisp cucumber, sliced red onion, green bell pepper, Kalamata olives, and a generous slab or crumbles of feta cheese. It's dressed simply with quality extra virgin olive oil, a splash of red wine vinegar, and a sprinkle of dried oregano.	Salad	\N	Tomatoes, cucumbers, red onion, green bell pepper, Kalamata olives, feta cheese (dairy), extra virgin olive oil, red wine vinegar, dried oregano, salt, pepper. [Note: Authentically, lettuce is not included.]	t	f	t	f	t	\N	2025-05-27 15:15:23.016207	2025-05-27 15:15:23.016207	{"dietary_flags_list": ["VEGETARIAN_OPTION", "GLUTEN_FREE_OPTION", "LOW_CARB (relatively)", "MEDITERRANEAN_DIET"], "allergen_alert_list": ["CONTAINS_DAIRY (feta cheese)", "CONTAINS_SULPHITES (red wine vinegar, olives may contain)"], "key_preparation_notes": "The classic Greek salad with fresh vegetables, olives, feta, and a simple oil/vinegar dressing.", "nutritional_highlights": {"fat": {"max": 35, "min": 20, "unit": "g"}, "carbs": {"max": 15, "min": 8, "unit": "g"}, "fiber": {"max": 5, "min": 2, "unit": "g"}, "protein": {"max": 10, "min": 6, "unit": "g"}, "calories": {"max": 400, "min": 250, "unit": "kcal"}}, "guidance_for_customer_short": "A truly authentic and refreshing Greek village salad.", "suitable_for_diet_preferences": []}	0.00	horiatiki
Lahanosalata (Greek Coleslaw) - Green and red shredded cabbage, grated carrots, olive oil and lemon juice	Lahanosalata is a simple and refreshing Greek cabbage salad, akin to a light coleslaw but typically without mayonnaise. It features finely shredded green and/or red cabbage, often with grated carrots, dressed with extra virgin olive oil and fresh lemon juice, and sometimes includes herbs like dill or parsley.	Salad / Side Dish	\N	Green cabbage, red cabbage (optional), carrots, extra virgin olive oil, fresh lemon juice, salt, black pepper, fresh dill or parsley (optional). [Note: Specific ingredients may vary slightly.]	t	t	t	t	t	\N	2025-05-27 15:15:23.106432	2025-05-27 15:15:23.106432	{"dietary_flags_list": ["VEGAN_OPTION", "VEGETARIAN_OPTION", "PLANT_BASED", "GLUTEN_FREE_OPTION", "LOW_CALORIE", "HIGH_FIBER"], "allergen_alert_list": [], "key_preparation_notes": "A light and tangy Greek cabbage salad with an olive oil and lemon dressing.", "nutritional_highlights": {"fat": {"max": 12, "min": 6, "unit": "g"}, "carbs": {"max": 15, "min": 8, "unit": "g"}, "fiber": {"max": 6, "min": 3, "unit": "g"}, "protein": {"max": 3, "min": 1, "unit": "g"}, "calories": {"max": 150, "min": 80, "unit": "kcal"}}, "guidance_for_customer_short": "Crisp and refreshing Greek-style coleslaw.", "suitable_for_diet_preferences": ["VEGAN_DIET", "VEGETARIAN_DIET", "MEDITERRANEAN_DIET", "PALEO_FRIENDLY"]}	0.00	lahanosalata
Maroulosalata (Greek Romaine Salad) - Shredded romaine lettuce, scallions, mixed herbs, olive oil, lemon juice	Maroulosalata is a delicate and refreshing Greek salad made with finely shredded romaine lettuce, fresh scallions (spring onions), and an abundance of fresh dill and sometimes other mixed herbs. It's dressed very simply with extra virgin olive oil and fresh lemon juice.	Salad	\N	Romaine lettuce, scallions (spring onions), fresh dill, fresh parsley (optional), extra virgin olive oil, fresh lemon juice, salt, black pepper. [Note: Herb combination may vary slightly.]	t	t	t	t	t	\N	2025-05-27 15:15:23.196542	2025-05-27 15:15:23.196542	{"dietary_flags_list": ["VEGAN_OPTION", "VEGETARIAN_OPTION", "PLANT_BASED", "GLUTEN_FREE_OPTION", "LOW_CALORIE"], "allergen_alert_list": [], "key_preparation_notes": "A light and refreshing salad of shredded romaine, scallions, and fresh herbs with a lemon-oil dressing.", "nutritional_highlights": {"fat": {"max": 12, "min": 6, "unit": "g"}, "carbs": {"max": 7, "min": 3, "unit": "g"}, "fiber": {"max": 3, "min": 1, "unit": "g"}, "protein": {"max": 2, "min": 1, "unit": "g"}, "calories": {"max": 140, "min": 70, "unit": "kcal"}}, "guidance_for_customer_short": "Delicate Greek romaine salad with fresh herbs and a zesty dressing.", "suitable_for_diet_preferences": ["VEGAN_DIET", "VEGETARIAN_DIET", "MEDITERRANEAN_DIET", "KETO_FRIENDLY", "PALEO_FRIENDLY"]}	0.00	maroulosalata
Patatosalata - Warm potato salad with sliced red onions, Kalamata olives, parsley and extra virgin olive oil	A Greek-style potato salad (Patatosalata) typically served warm or at room temperature. It features boiled or steamed potatoes tossed with sliced red onions, Kalamata olives, fresh parsley, and a generous dressing of extra virgin olive oil and often lemon juice or red wine vinegar. Unlike American potato salad, it does not usually contain mayonnaise.	Salad / Side Dish	\N	Potatoes (waxy variety like Yukon Gold or new potatoes), red onions, Kalamata olives, fresh parsley, extra virgin olive oil, lemon juice or red wine vinegar, salt, black pepper. [Note: Dressing ingredients may vary slightly.]	t	t	t	t	t	\N	2025-05-27 15:15:23.285384	2025-05-27 15:15:23.285384	{"dietary_flags_list": ["VEGAN_OPTION", "VEGETARIAN_OPTION", "PLANT_BASED", "GLUTEN_FREE_OPTION"], "allergen_alert_list": ["CONTAINS_SULPHITES (if vinegar or some olives used)"], "key_preparation_notes": "Warm potato salad with red onions, olives, parsley, and an olive oil based dressing.", "nutritional_highlights": {"fat": {"max": 20, "min": 10, "unit": "g"}, "carbs": {"max": 40, "min": 25, "unit": "g"}, "fiber": {"max": 6, "min": 3, "unit": "g"}, "protein": {"max": 6, "min": 3, "unit": "g"}, "calories": {"max": 350, "min": 200, "unit": "kcal"}}, "guidance_for_customer_short": "Hearty and flavorful Greek potato salad, served warm.", "suitable_for_diet_preferences": ["VEGAN_DIET", "VEGETARIAN_DIET", "MEDITERRANEAN_DIET"]}	0.00	patatosalata
Dakos Bread Salad - Fresh tomatoes, barley rusks, feta, capers, onion, oregano, and basil	Dakos (or Ntakos) is a traditional Cretan salad or meze. It features a base of Paximadia (hard barley rusks) that are lightly moistened, then topped with grated or chopped fresh tomatoes, crumbled feta or mizithra cheese, capers, red onion, olives (often), and fresh herbs like oregano and basil, all drizzled with extra virgin olive oil.	Salad / Appetizer	\N	Barley rusks (paximadia - wheat/barley), fresh tomatoes, feta cheese (dairy) or mizithra cheese (dairy), capers, red onion, Kalamata olives (often), fresh oregano, fresh basil, extra virgin olive oil, salt, pepper. [Note: Specific cheese and inclusion of olives may vary.]	t	f	f	f	t	\N	2025-05-27 15:15:23.376287	2025-05-27 15:15:23.376287	{"dietary_flags_list": ["VEGETARIAN_OPTION", "MEDITERRANEAN_DIET"], "allergen_alert_list": ["CONTAINS_WHEAT (barley rusks often contain wheat flour as well)", "CONTAINS_GLUTEN (barley)", "CONTAINS_DAIRY (feta/mizithra cheese)", "CONTAINS_SULPHITES (capers, olives may contain)"], "key_preparation_notes": "A Cretan salad built on barley rusks, topped with tomatoes, feta, and herbs. Contains gluten and dairy.", "nutritional_highlights": {"fat": {"max": 28, "min": 15, "unit": "g"}, "carbs": {"max": 40, "min": 25, "unit": "g"}, "fiber": {"max": 8, "min": 4, "unit": "g"}, "protein": {"max": 15, "min": 8, "unit": "g"}, "calories": {"max": 450, "min": 280, "unit": "kcal"}}, "guidance_for_customer_short": "A hearty and flavorful Cretan bread salad with fresh toppings.", "suitable_for_diet_preferences": []}	0.00	dakos
Tabouli - Chopped parsley, cous-cous, tomato, cucumber, mint, red onion and lemon-tahini dressing	A refreshing Middle Eastern-inspired salad made with finely chopped parsley as the primary ingredient, mixed with couscous (as specified, though traditional tabouli uses bulgur), diced tomatoes, cucumber, fresh mint, and red onion. This version is tossed in a creamy and zesty lemon-tahini dressing.	Salad / Side Dish	\N	Fresh parsley, couscous (wheat), tomatoes, cucumber, fresh mint, red onion, lemon juice, tahini (sesame paste), extra virgin olive oil (optional in dressing), salt, pepper. [Note: Specific proportions and dressing ingredients may vary.]	t	t	f	t	t	\N	2025-05-27 15:19:42.354298	2025-05-27 15:19:42.354298	{"dietary_flags_list": ["VEGAN_OPTION", "VEGETARIAN_OPTION", "PLANT_BASED"], "allergen_alert_list": ["CONTAINS_WHEAT (couscous)", "CONTAINS_SESAME (tahini)"], "key_preparation_notes": "A vibrant parsley and couscous salad (note: couscous instead of traditional bulgur) with a creamy lemon-tahini dressing. Contains wheat and sesame.", "nutritional_highlights": {"fat": {"max": 20, "min": 10, "unit": "g"}, "carbs": {"max": 40, "min": 25, "unit": "g"}, "fiber": {"max": 8, "min": 4, "unit": "g"}, "protein": {"max": 9, "min": 5, "unit": "g"}, "calories": {"max": 350, "min": 200, "unit": "kcal"}}, "guidance_for_customer_short": "A refreshing herb-packed salad with couscous and lemon-tahini dressing.", "suitable_for_diet_preferences": ["VEGAN_DIET", "VEGETARIAN_DIET"]}	0.00	tabouli
